# üß© Installing a Power BI Custom Connector

This guide walks through installing a Power BI custom connector on both the **Microsoft Store** and **Download (MSI installer)** versions of Power BI Desktop. It includes folder paths, security settings, and troubleshooting tips.

---

## üìÅ Folder Locations

| Version                  | Folder Path                                                                 |
|--------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Microsoft Store**      | `C:\Users\<YourUser>\Documents\Power BI Desktop\Custom Connectors`          |
| **Download (MSI)**       | `C:\Users\<YourUser>\Documents\Microsoft Power BI Desktop\Custom Connectors`|

> If the `Custom Connectors` folder doesn‚Äôt exist, create it manually.

---

## üì¶ Installing the Connector

1. Copy your `.mez`, `.pq`, `.pqx`, or `.m` file into the appropriate folder.
2. Right-click the file ‚Üí **Properties** ‚Üí Check **Unblock** if present.
3. Open Power BI Desktop.
4. Go to **File** ‚Üí **Options and settings** ‚Üí **Options**.
5. Under **Global** ‚Üí **Security**, find **Data Extensions**.
6. Choose one of the following:

| Option                                                                 | Description                                                                 |
|------------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| ‚úÖ **Only allow Microsoft certified and trusted extensions**           | Blocks uncertified connectors unless signed or explicitly allowed.         |
| ‚ö†Ô∏è **Allow any extension to load without validation**                  | Enables all connectors, including uncertified ones. Use only if trusted.   |

7. Click **OK** and **restart Power BI Desktop**.

---

## üîê Security Considerations

- Uncertified connectors may bypass privacy levels and transmit credentials insecurely.
- Use the ‚ÄúAllow any extension‚Ä¶‚Äù setting only if you trust the source.
- For enterprise deployment, consider **signing the connector** with a certificate.

---

## üß† Troubleshooting Tips

- Confirm the file is in the correct folder for your version.
- Ensure Power BI Desktop is restarted after changing settings.
- Check for Windows file blocking (Unblock checkbox).
- Use the latest version of Power BI Desktop.

